<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-073-039 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 056 877</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  Sept 1991 v8 n9 p208(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Animation Works 1.0. (Software Review) (8-bit color animationprogram from Gold Disk) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pogue, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Gold Disk Inc's Animation Works 1.0 provides true Disney-style celanimation on the Macintosh.andP;  Animation Works is the first programto provide stand-alone color cel animations for under $2,000.andP;  Theprogram automates the task of painting every frame individuallyand provides a strong, but simple, interface and well-selectedfeature set.andP;  The animations are very memory intensive and speedis slow on the Mac.andP;  The manual could use some improvement.andP;  Atleast 2Mbytes of RAM are recommended and a hard drive is neededfor long color movies.andP;  The list price is $199.95.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gold Disk Software Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Animation Works (Computer graphics software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationAnimationComputer animationGraphics software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>